				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10308001#post-4426366</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10308001/scp-4460#post-4426366</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 18 Nov 2019 16:14:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>llesiows</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3430205</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So it's a spooky natural gas factory (?) in nebraska from the 30s (?) in pristine condition for some reason with a russian factory-headed guy wandering around a hidden section of the factory telling dad jokes. I don't much understand the concept and it seems to go nowhere. I also have some questions;</p> <p>How did the d-class get separated from his group and pass out?<br /> How did the foundation know there were 8 floors to the hidden section, and know that they needed to get to the bottom?<br /> Why didn't the D-class get equipped with things to protect against the laughing gas? (or maybe they did but it wasn't clear)<br /> Why is it in russian if it's in Nebraska in the 30s (or around then)?<br /> How did the D-class know ОТЕЦ's name? (I know he says he &quot;knew it from the start&quot; or something like that, but it wasn't made clear whether it has a memetic effect on anyone, same goes for the little disclaimer before the &quot;jokes&quot; why would the foundation put it there if it's so arbitrary as some personnel &quot;feeling embarrassed&quot; because of the jokes, and if it is memetic, they likely wouldn't have put them there)</p> <p>Overall, some problems with the concept in general, lots of work is needed to make things more clear, and I'm just confused. -1 until some things can be fixed.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
